            <mods:abstract>Mona Lisa is a half-length portrait painting by the Italian Renaissance artist Leonardo da Vinci that has been described as "the best known, the most visited, the most written about, the most sung about, the most parodied work of art in the world". It is also one of the most valuable paintings in the world. On 21 August 1911, the paiting was stolen from the Louvre. In 1913 the thief was discovered attempting to sell the painting. The painting was returned to the Louvre, where it resided today.</mods:abstract>
